author: Brianne Tolj For Daily Mail Australia
title: Syndey house has remained untouched since the 1920s
text:
A Sydney home up for sale for the first time in 90 years is sending potential buyers back in time with its floral wallpaper, marble fireplaces and 1920s decor.
The four-bedroom Victorian home in Marrickville is set for auction on February 17 for buyers to renovate or re-develop the land, according to realestate.com.au .
Floral carpet and wallpaper are splashed across what appears to be every room in the charming 860sqm home with a large back yard.
A four-bedroom Victorian home in Sydney is up for sale for the first time in 90 years and is sending potential buyers back in time with its 1920s decor (pictured)
The charming 860sqm home in Marrickville is decorated with floral carpet and matching wallpaper, the original mouldings and four marble fireplaces (pictured)
It is set for auction on February 17 for buyers to renovate or re-develop the land
The original mouldings, skirting and four large, grey marble fireplaces accent the vintage decor.
A verandah wraps around the house beginning from the stained glass front door.
The home's entrance leads to a long hallway with floral white architraves and prominent chandelier.
A small vintage television that appears to be from the 60s and Victorian gold couches decorate the large living room.
The home's entrance leads to a long hallway with floral white architraves and prominent chandelier (pictured)
The bedrooms are also generous in size and a single bed sits in at least two of the rooms (pictured)
A study, dining room and sunroom are featured at the back of the home
